alert.note: Alert for Kewaunee (Wisconsin) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.senderName: NWS GreenBay (East Central Wisconsin - Green Bay)
info.headline: Flood Warning issued April 01 at 11:56AM CDT until further notice by NWS GreenBay
info.description: ...The National Weather Service in Green Bay WI has issued a Flood Warning for the following rivers in Wisconsin... Kewaunee River near Kewaunee affecting Kewaunee County. ...FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT FROM THIS MORNING UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring. * WHERE...Kewaunee River near Kewaunee. * WHEN...From this morning until further notice. * IMPACTS...At 14.0 feet, Water approaches Ransom Moore Lane near highway FF. Streamflow upstream may become faster due to increasing elevation as well as localized flooding. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 11:00 AM CDT Saturday the stage was 14.2 feet. - Forecast...No forecast is available for this location. - Flood stage is 14.0 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued late tonight.
